menu "NPU Support Network Feature Configuration"

config MTK_NPU_ADPT_FWD
	bool "MediaTek NPU Adapter Forward Support"
	default n
	help
	  Select y to support adapter forward network feature with MediaTek
	  NPU hardware.
	  This feature is a special request to bridge WAN with another network
	  port when NPU receives specific type of packet.
	  This feature is not expected to be enabled in normal scenario.

config MTK_NPU_L4S
	bool "MediaTek NPU L4S Support"
	default n
	help
	  Select y to support L4S network feature with MediaTek NPU hardware.
	  This feature is a special request to implement L4S functionalities
	  with NPU hardware to support network congestion control, however,
	  NPU can only approximately predict network status. Thus, the feature
	  may not be able to provide percise network congestion status and it
	  should be used with caution and tune it finely.
	  In addition, other features is not compatible with this feature. In
	  other words, if L4S is enabled, other NPU features cannot be
	  supported.
	  This feature is not expected to be enabled in normal scenario.

config MTK_NPU_RATE_LIMIT
	bool "MediaTek NPU Rate Limit Support"
	default n
	help
	  Select y to support MediaTek NPU forward certain type of packets to
	  with QoS control.
	  This feature is a special request and it supports 4 type of QoS queue
	  to forward those pre-defined packet types.
	  This feature is not expected to be enabled in normal scenario.

endmenu
